Introducing the Life R4Ever Kent Project

The LIFE R4ever Kent project was established in 2021 and runs for 5 years. Nestled in the breath-taking landscape of South Cumbria, in the Lake District National Park the River Kent winds its way from headwaters around Kentmere and flows through Kendal to meet the sea in Morcambe Bay.

Sometimes wild and flashy, sometimes sluggish and brackish, the River system has its beauties and hidden depths. Held dear by residents for its nature, the project aims to Restore and Revitalise this majestic river system, ensuring it is Resilient to current pressures and future changes.

Stay tuned for our new website coming soon which will have more information about this fantastic river and its species, what the project has accomplished, what we have yet to do, who is involved and how you can be too.
